Check if group is complete

Source: R/dvidtools.R
manc_check_group_complete.Rd

In other words if the body_ids argument contains all neurons in the group.

Usage

manc_check_group_complete(group_id, body_ids, conn = manc_neuprint())

Arguments

group_id

numeric/character with group id

body_ids

vector with body ids to compare

conn

Optional, a neuprint_connection object, which also specifies the neuPrint server. Defaults to manc_neuprint() to ensure that query is against the VNC dataset.

Value

logical TRUE if group is complete, FALSE otherwise.
